      <title>Bring back, Discord (PVP) Server</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=PVP&amp;message.id=11529#M11529</link>
      <description>&lt;div&gt;A new server is needed for pvp, but do you remember the Discord server? It was out for about 6 weeks before the discord expansion.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Everyone could attack everyone, no limits&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;If you died for any reason: pk, drowned, fall off a cliff, you go back to level 1&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;triple experience all the time&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;If a player killed you, they could loot all your gear&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;One character per server&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;This was the BEST pvp fun I have ever had on EQ or any other game.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;While it was out, I was a barbarian and hunting in Everfrost with about 140 other barbarians, fighting for each kill, after we starting hitting level 6, a ton of fights, but eventually we worked together to get stronger as a nation, then went into Blackburrow to level, and on out into Qeynos Hills where we fought the humans. It was like a huge world of Risk, where you built up your army then went to attack the next territory.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;If this was a permanent server then guilds would have formed and more alliances etc, still it was the most hardcore pvp server ever, and it was the most fun. Talk about a fear of death, you where focused constantly, it was great, and even with newer games out, a server like this would attract alot of players.&lt;/div&gt;</description>
